    {"id": "event_aldenheim", "keywords": ["aldenheim", "fall of aldenheim", "lament of kings", "earthforge", "house buarath"], "priority": 9, "content": "Aldenheim fell three centuries ago when House Buarath seized the EarthForge beneath it. Before the fall it was a center of learning. The site is called the Lament of Kings and draws annual pilgrimages."},
    {"id": "event_deceivers_war", "keywords": ["deceivers war", "domnathar invasion", "running war", "deceivers' war"], "priority": 9, "content": "The Deceivers' War was a cataclysmic invasion by the Domnathar. The main host marched north through the Steppe. Far Riders and Pasua intercepted them in the Running War. Dark Dawn on the ninth night was the climax -- one in ten survived, but the Kin held."},
    {"id": "event_dark_dawn", "keywords": ["dark dawn", "dark dawn battlefield", "battle of dark dawn"], "priority": 8, "content": "Dark Dawn Battlefield covers forty square miles on the Eternal Steppe. Kin-sense flickers across it; the center is a dead zone. Glass-fused craters mark the site. Horses shy and a smell of hot pitch rises on windless nights."},
    {"id": "event_shattering", "keywords": ["shattering", "shattering of man", "concordant collapse"], "priority": 9, "content": "The Shattering was the catastrophic failure of the Eke Concordant when the Third Crowned Keeper proved too feeble. Oasis thrones were abandoned, rune-circles failed, and the continent's political structure fractured permanently."},
    {"id": "event_silence_breach", "keywords": ["silence breach", "expanding anomaly", "void incursion", "dorrach kael"], "priority": 8, "content": "The Silence Breach is an expanding anomaly in Gatefall where Kin-sense fails entirely. Creatures from within register as nothing. The Gatefall Remnant monitors its growth. It is one of the world's greatest mysteries."},
    {"id": "concept_kin_sense", "keywords": ["kin-sense", "kin sense", "elemental sixth sense", "resonance detection"], "priority": 9, "content": "Kin-sense is the elemental sixth sense shared by all Kin races. It detects resonance within 60 feet, passes through 5-foot barriers, cannot be dispelled. Nine categories: Harmonic (Kin), Wild Static (beasts), Null (Silentborn), Void (Domnathar), Echo (dreaming), None (undead/Farborn), Raw Static (elementals)."},
    {"id": "concept_elemental_lords", "keywords": ["elemental lords", "four creators", "lord of stone", "lady of fire", "lady of the sea", "youngest brother"], "priority": 9, "content": "Four Elemental Lords shaped Oreka: Lord of Stone (comatose), Lady of Fire (active, volatile), Lady of the Sea (active, patient), Youngest Brother/Wind Lord (exiled, return prophesied). They influence through elemental resonance and Kin-sense."},
    {"id": "concept_ascended_gods", "keywords": ["ascended gods", "mortal apotheosis", "nine gods"], "priority": 8, "content": "Nine mortals achieved divinity after Aldenheim: Dagdan (United Sun), Harreem (Golden Rose), Kailea (Waves), Cinvarin (Five Witnesses), Semyon (Hearth Mother), Apela Kelsoe (Windrider), Ludus Galerius (Stone's Hand), Gonmareck (Anvil Saint), The Hand Unanswered."},
    {"id": "concept_domnathar", "keywords": ["domnathar", "deceivers", "void resonance", "alien invaders"], "priority": 9, "content": "The Domnathar are the Deceivers -- an alien civilization that invaded Oreka. They register as Void on Kin-sense. They enslaved Farborn, Goblins, and Wargs as infantry. Remnants survive as the Shattered Host in hidden strongholds."},
    {"id": "concept_deceivers_feat", "keywords": ["deceiver's feat", "deceivers feat", "kin-sense suppression", "unstrung practice"], "priority": 7, "content": "The Deceiver's Feat is the forbidden art of suppressing one's Kin-sense signature, becoming invisible to detection. Practiced by The Unstrung criminal organization."},
